which is I actually
started from an etching

01:30:55.410 --> 01:31:00.690
by the Spanish artist Francisco
Goya called the "The Sleep

01:31:00.690 --> 01:31:04.150
of Reason Produces Monsters"
and it kind of resonated

01:31:04.150 --> 01:31:09.710
with the events of last year
what with Brexit and Trump's a;

01:31:09.710 --> 01:31:11.890
you know I started sort
of dropping singles now.

01:31:11.890 --> 01:31:14.840
I've got another one coming out
next month and the month after.

01:31:14.840 --> 01:31:17.580
It seems to be a practical
way of getting stuff

01:31:17.580 --> 01:31:19.690
out that has too much
[inaudible] than making records.

01:31:19.690 --> 01:31:20.990
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winick: Right.

01:31:20.990 --> 01:31:22.290
&gt;&gt; Billy Bragg: Just put the
songs out when they're ready.

01:31:22.290 --> 01:31:23.590
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winick: So, is
that what you're doing now?

01:31:23.590 --> 01:31:24.890
You're doing?

01:31:24.890 --> 01:31:26.190
&gt;&gt; Billy Bragg: Yeah.

01:31:26.190 --> 01:31:27.490
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winick: Song-by-song?

01:31:27.490 --> 01:31:28.790
&gt;&gt; Billy Bragg: One
of them will come

01:31:28.790 --> 01:31:30.090
out between now and Christmas.

01:31:30.090 --> 01:31:31.390
And we'll probably compile
them on a CD probably.

01:31:31.390 --> 01:31:32.690
&gt;&gt; Stephen Winick: Alright.

